routine; namely to defend your realm and attack the others. I really like having something like this in the game, it makes for a pleasent change that you can hopefully accomplish something and that all your wonderful equipment and fighting skills can be put to some sort of use when you have reached the lofty heights of uberness <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Trade skills</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>They were a pain in EQ and they still take up horrible amounts of time, but at least they don't require farming for pelts and they were there to begin with and we didn't have to wait 2 years for them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Uber items ?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>Unlike other games that I know <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Equipment is entirely secondary to skill at playing your character. In a resonably balanced RvR fight, victory will go to the person who chooses his ground, forces the enemy to fight at a disadvantage, achieves the element of surprise or otherwise is skillful enough to stack the odds against the enemy.<br>As it should be.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Fighting pace</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>DAoC is much more fast paced than EQ. In EQ, fights could take upwards of several minutes to complete, not here, most fights doesn't last above a minute and the RvR fights are much much faster than that. Pro or Con ? You decide.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Mythic</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>They actually listen and have a tendency to fix problems that needs to be fixed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Some people (*waves at Utnayan*) have a habit of seeing this as a conspiracy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>That sounds lovely doesn't it, so where are the cons ? Well, there are a few:<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Roleplaying</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>This is of course a big issue to me, but due both to the fast paced nature of the game as well as a lack of background for the world, it is extremely difficult to get any roleplaying done EXCEPT on the roleplay servers. The RP servers are a different story, they have a lot of dedicated and industrious people in this department.<br>Of course, with my luck Winterblood choose to play on a non-RP server, the gits. But I'll get back at them when we go to Star Wars Galaxies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> The game is incomplete</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>This is being said of every new online game that comes out, but it is still no excuse. At launch DAoC was very very limited in scope. But it is my opinion that the game has potential and that Mythic is going to fulfill it.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Bugs</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>Not a terribly big problem, they are lightyears ahead of Verant in finding and fixing bugs, but they still pop up and in the early stages of the game it was downright annyoing to have your castle-burning-army crash the server and make the NPC guards that you had just killed reappear.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Going to become Ever Dark Age ?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>Mythic is adding content at a frantic pace, sometimes too frantic perhaps. Their latest contribution of significant size are a very very difficult zone for each of the realms that houses a dragon.<br>Note that these are not the pussi-wussie dragons of EQ, these are real army-killers, not something you can take down with 2 groups.<br>All well and fine, the problem is that the difficulty of this zone seems to have forced people back into the EQ mentality. Lists are being kept for groups, greed prevaletes and people are downright obnoxious. <br>The strange thing is that its only in this zone that it is that way.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Level difference in RvR</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>To my great regret, DAoC is a level-based game (I'm beginning to hate those) And the foregone conclusion is of course that a level 50 character can whip the buttocks of 5 level 30 characters without breaking a sweat. This has resulted in the fact that if you try to venture out on the battlefields at less than level 35 then your chances of survival are not very great.<br>As a footnote to this it should be said that yesterday we just got 3 seperate 'Arena-zones' so to speak, where only people who are within level range of the rest can go. I'm told they are very fun. (I'm too highlevel to go there :P) <br><br>-Elhimac. Commander of the Phantom Guard-<br>-Whereabouts unknown-<br><br>-Halcime. Skald of the Greyrunners-<br>-Midgaard, Morgan le Fay- <p><IMG SRC=http://www.sitecenter.dk/darkelf/nss-folder/scrapbog/elhimac5.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF7D6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uavimoththex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avimoth Thex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#6C8361>(3/20/02 1:01:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsroleplayforum.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Dal's questions<